
@startuml

class Student {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +email: string
  +coursesRegistered: List<Course>
  +requestAppointment(course: Course, date: Date, time: Time)
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +email: string
  +coursesTaught: List<Course>
  +acceptAppointment(appointment: Appointment)
}

class Course {
  +id: int
  +name: string
  +description: string
  +studentsEnrolled: List<Student>
  +teachingAssistants: List<TeachingAssistant>
}

class Appointment {
  +id: int
  +student: Student
  +ta: TeachingAssistant
  +course: Course
  +date: Date
  +time: Time
  +status: Status
}

enum Status {
  PENDING, ACCEPTED, REJECTED, COMPLETED
}

Student "1" -- "many" Course : registeredFor
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "many" Course : teaches
Course "1" -- "many" Appointment : has
Student "1" -- "1" Appointment : requests
TeachingAssistant "1" -- "1" Appointment : handles

@enduml

### Explanation of Relationships:
- A **Student** can be registered for **multiple Courses**.
- A **Teaching Assistant** can teach **multiple Courses**.
- A **Course** can have **multiple Appointments**.
- Each **Appointment** is associated with one **Student**, one **Teaching Assistant**, and one **Course**.
- The **Status** enum defines the possible states of an appointment.

